accepted_collaterals_count.descr: Count of different collateral types accepted by the protocol

active_loan_records.descr: Total number of active loans in the system

admin_account.descr: Administrative account with privileged access to protocol functions

base_bps.descr: Minimum APR at 0% utilization (basis points per year).

base_token_id.descr: The main lending token used for deposits and borrowing (0 for ALGO)

borrow_index_wad.descr: Multiplicative borrow index (scaled by INDEX_SCALE). Starts at INDEX_SCALE

buyout_token_id.descr: Total number of active loans in the system

circulating_lst.descr: Total LST tokens currently in circulation (represents depositor claims)

debug_diff.descr: Difference between max borrow and requested (for debugging)

ema_alpha_bps.descr: (Optional) Utilization EMA weight in bps (0..10_000; 0 disables smoothing).

kink_norm_bps.descr: Kink point on normalized utilization (0..10_000 across [0..util_cap]).

last_accrual_ts.descr: Timestamp (ledger seconds) at which borrow_index_wad was last advanced

last_apr_bps.descr: APR (in bps) that applied during [last_accrual_ts, now) before recompute

last_max_borrow.descr: Last calculated maximum borrowable amount in USD (for debugging)

last_requested_loan.descr: Last requested loan amount in USD (for debugging)

liq_bonus_bps.descr: Liquidation bonus in bps (e.g., 500 = 5% bonus to liquidators)

liq_threshold_bps.descr: Liquidation threshold (e.g., 8500 = 85% - liquidate when CR falls below)

lst_token_id.descr: LST (Liquidity Staking Token) representing depositor shares in the pool

ltv_bps.descr: Loan-to-Value ratio (e.g., 7500 = 75% max borrowing against collateral)

max_apr_bps.descr: (Optional) Absolute APR ceiling in bps (0 = no cap).

max_apr_step_bps.descr: (Optional) Max APR change per accrual step in bps (0 = no limit).

oracle_app.descr: External oracle application for asset price feeds

origination_fee_bps.descr: One-time fee charged on loan origination (e.g., 100 = 1%)

power_gamma_q16.descr: (Optional) Power-curve exponent γ in Q16.16 fixed-point.

prev_apr_bps.descr: (Optional, mutable) Last applied APR in bps (for step limiting).

slope1_bps.descr: APR increase from 0 → kink (added to base) over the normalized range.

slope2_bps.descr: APR increase from kink → cap (added after kink) over the normalized range.

total_borrows.descr: Total outstanding borrower principal + accrued interest (debt)

total_borrows_principal.descr: Sum of borrower principals (no interest). We’ll migrate total_borrows usage.

total_deposits.descr: Total underlying assets deposited in the protocol

util_cap_bps.descr: Hard utilization cap in bps (e.g., 8000 = 80% of deposits may be borrowed).

util_ema_bps.descr: (Optional, mutable) Stored EMA of normalized utilization in bps.
